# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
# Everything (HTML included) revalidates on each load: the browser sends a
# conditional request and gets a tiny 304 when nothing changed, or the fresh
# file the instant it does. This is the fix for "I pushed but my browser still
# shows the old version" — it covers the HTML page itself, not just CSS/JS.
# Images are allowed to cache for a day since they rarely change.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
